{
  "texts": [
    "These are a fundamental part of explanation and learning (Chi et al., 1989).",
    "For the question \"What is 12/4?",
    "\", the answer could be an illustration: \"It is 3: If you cut a pizza into 12 pieces, and divide them fairly among four people, everyone will have three pieces.\"",
    "While the illustration may not reflect how the explainer arrived at the answer, they expect that it will help the explainee understand the answer.",
    "In this section, we introduce our data and annotation setup."
  ]
}